"This is not the company I built." Denton argued with Gawker's editors over their decision to publish a post on Thursday night about Condé Nast C.F.O. David Geithner allegedly arranging to hire a male escort. It was irresponsible for the editors to publish the post without considering the harm that it could do to Geithner, he said. "I don't want some guy blowing his brains out and that being on our hands," he said.
